      <div class="msgContentFrame">VIT is the most important stat because the apparent effects of +strength and +dex are minimal at best. A long time ago I've heard people say it was something like 20 strength = +6% damage on a marauder. +6% DPS is good, but in my opinion, not as good as +VIT. On a Lancer, 20 VIT = an extra hit, maybe two from a monster. That's the difference between life and death. Death debuff will kill your SP gains much more than anything else in this entire game, especially considering that during the time you run back from the aetherial gate --&gt; camp, you're getting 0 SP. And that Raise gives death debuff on revive. +6% Damage maybe give you like 3 extra SP on damage procs.  <br /> <br />What I would say to you is to get Ferocity and Raging Strike on your bar. It is completely possible to do a Heavy thrust (Miss) --&gt; Ferocity --&gt; Raging Strike --&gt; Feint for massive SP procs, and they use extremely little stamina for a 2x-3x hit. <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 16th 2010  1:54pm by Meowshi </span></i></div>
